parameters: That's right... When we first met...
She was very scared back then...
Unable to leave the village... unaware of the outside world...
Umi: "The sunset was so beautiful... I got lost in it..."
And now... here... Umi is here...
The Umi who disappeared back then...
Umi: "What's wrong, Kru...? Why are you crying so much...?"

Back then... living with just Mia... the wounds from being separated from
our father and mother hadn't healed...
Umi: "Did you have a scary dream? There, there, let Umi pat you..."
But to not let that loneliness show... she always pretended to be strong...
Even so, when she was eating meat, she looked truly happy...
And she dreamed of seeing the sea...
Umi: "There, there... It's not scary anymore..."

Umi: "...Kru... What's wrong? Aren't you going to get angry like you
usually do?"
Umi has become a mother and raised her child up to this point...
The fingers that were once supple and soft are now stiff, dry, and chapped.

The backs of her hands are red with fine cuts, and her legs have several
purple bruises.

The short and lustrous hair has grown long, and with that length, it has
become damaged and lost its shine. The length of her hair told the story of
the time that had passed...

With every moment of that passed time... I found the Umi here unbearably
dear...

The parts that hadn't changed brought back memories of the past and gave me
a smile...

The parts that had changed gave me the courage and vitality to step into
tomorrow...
For me... for Umi... and for Mia...
Umi: "What's gotten into you all of a sudden?"
Kru: "I will love Umi and Mia... forever..."
Umi: "...Even when Umi becomes a wrinkled old lady?"
No matter how much time passes...
Umi: "Even if Umi... eats too much meat and gets fat and big?"
No matter how much she changes...
That's right... When we first met...
She was very timid back then...
Unable to leave the village... Unaware of the outside world...
Umi: "Umi... doesn't deserve to be found by Kru..."
Umi: "Umi can make it on her own!"

Living with Mia, and deep down, the wounds from being separated from her
father and mother hadn't healed...

Umi: "Umi's recipes... they're really popular... and the shop's gotten so
busy!"
But she always pretended to be strong, not to let that loneliness show...
Umi: "There are so many people who want to marry Umi..."

But even with such wounds, she looked truly happy when she was eating
meat...
Umi: "Even people of high status... and those with lots of money..."
And she dreamed of seeing the ocean...
Umi: "...Umi... has hurt Kru so much..."
Kru: "...It was born from Umi, right?"

Against the backdrop of the sea illuminated by the setting sun, Umi cried
out loud...

Umi had become a mother and raised her child up to this point... She must
have blamed herself and, just as tightly, worked hard to discipline
herself...
Her once supple and soft fingers had become stiff, dry, and rough.

The backs of her hands were red with small cuts, and her legs had several
purple bruises.

Her short and lustrous hair had grown out, becoming damaged and losing its
shine. The length of her grown hair told the story of the time that had
passed...

With every moment that passed... Umi in my arms became unbearably dear to
me...

The parts of her that hadn't changed brought back memories of the past and
gave me a smile...

The parts that had changed gave me the courage and vitality to step into
tomorrow...
For me... for Umi... and for Mia... towards our future together...
Kru: "I will love Umi and Mia... forever..."
Umi: "...Even when Umi becomes a wrinkled old lady?"
Umi: "Even if Umi... eats too much meat and gets fat and big?"
